          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-19485 lnet: Deprecate ip2nets and routes params",
        "message": "LU-19485 lnet: Deprecate ip2nets and routes params\n\nLNet currently supports network and routing configuration via kernel\nmodule parameters (ip2nets= and routes=) supplied at module load time\n(e.g. via modprobe.conf). This approach is being deprecated in favor\nof Dynamic LNet Config (DLC) which uses user-space parsing of YAML +\nnetlink.\n\nModify the description of these parameters to note the deprecation,\nand issue a one-time warning at startup if these parameters are being\nused.\n\nSurround relevant code in a version macro so the code will\nautomatically \"disappear\" in Lustre 2.18.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nSigned-off-by: Chris Horn <chris.horn@hpe.com>\nChange-Id: Ifa60533c9a1362b9cb17c7451474e7a755a652c8\nReviewed-on: https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/61861\nReviewed-by: Serguei Smirnov <ssmirnov@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: James Simmons <jsimmons@infradead.org>\nTested-by: jenkins <devops@whamcloud.com>\nTested-by: Maloo <maloo@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <green@whamcloud.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
